ional level in Irish soccerand withinternational studies on track and field athletes.\", \"from\": 6200, \"to\": 6353, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6283, \"end\": 6288, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9998197676447944, \"rank\": 0.00017641800502139285, \"text\": \"Irish\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"This bias\", \"from\": 6200, \"to\": 6209}, {\"ngram\": \"early developers\", \"from\": 6218, \"to\": 6234}, {\"ngram\": \"research atnational level\", \"from\": 6254, \"to\": 6279}, {\"ngram\": \"track and field athletes\", \"from\": 6328, \"to\": 6352}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The clear message for parents and coaches is not to read too much into the performances of young adolescents as both stellar and mediocre performances can be misleading about future potential.\", \"from\": 6355, \"to\": 6547, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The clear message\", \"from\": 6355, \"to\": 6372}, {\"ngram\": \"parents\", \"from\": 6377, \"to\": 6384}, {\"ngram\": \"coaches\", \"from\": 6389, \"to\": 6396}, {\"ngram\": \"the performances\", \"from\": 6426, \"to\": 6442}, {\"ngram\": \"young adolescents\", \"from\": 6446, \"to\": 6463}, {\"ngram\": \"both stellar and mediocre performances\", \"from\": 6467, \"to\": 6505}, {\"ngram\": \"future potential\", \"from\": 6530, \"to\": 6546}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Instead, emphasise providing opportunities for as many children as possible to enjoy competing and feel like they are progressing.\", \"from\": 6548, \"to\": 6678, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"opportunities\", \"from\": 6577, \"to\": 6590}, {\"ngram\": \"as many children\", \"from\": 6595, \"to\": 6611}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The views expressed here are those of the author and do not represent or reflect the views of RT\\u00c9 University of Limerick Fo